<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Binzet" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma anatolica" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anatolica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
especially by its habit, calyx and corolla length. However, the new species differs mainly in its sterile shoots; a green-grey stem with adpressed setose trichomes, the setae arising from short stellate hairy and shortly hairy (not bluish-black, otherwise glabrous as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); sterile rosette leaves and basal leaves -50 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1,5(-1.8) mm, revolute-subulate; cauline leaves -20 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-1.5(-1.8) mm, (as opposed to 15-32 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5(-1.8) mm in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); an inflorescence of 1-2 cymes, sometimes elongated after flowering (not short subcapitate); flower bracts 8-15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1-2 mm, the apex acute (as opposed to 7-8 mm, apex lingulate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); pedicel 1-2 mm (not 1-1.5 mm); calyx 6-8 mm in flower, 8-12 mm in fruit, suboblate in shape, patent strigose on 
<normalizedToken originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
tubercles and shortly hairy on the outside and rarely hairy on the inside (as opposed to 10-11 mm, subobtuse, and hispid in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); corolla yellow, clavate, puberulous, lobes 1 mm long, 1.7 mm wide at base, widely triangular (as opposed to white, clavate-campanulate, glabrous, lobes short, acute in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Riedl" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma subulifolia" order="Boraginales" pageId="2" pageNumber="41" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subulifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="41">Onosma subulifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and nutlets 3-3.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-2.3 mm, short beaked, grey.
</paragraph>
