<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Flowering from May to June, setting fruit until late July.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="palynology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Palynology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
Pollen grains are heteropolar, trisyncolporate and subprolate. Exine surface of the grains is insular. The insulae have free scabrae and the scabrae are widely spaced. The average means of the number of scabrae in each insulae range from 6 to 15. The main palynological characters and SEM micrographs of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Binzet" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Onosma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Onosma anatolica" order="Boraginales" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anatolica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Onosma anatolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are presented in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Pollen morphological parameters of Onosma anatolica (W: Wodehouse Method)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/34EB17FC341262F333B1FFD7849EBF10" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" tableUuid="34EB17FC341262F333B1FFD7849EBF10">1</tableCitation>
and Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. SEM microphotograph of pollen of Onosma anatolica." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.69.8360.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/100488" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">5</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="nutlet morphology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Nutlet morphology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
